      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "EVERY LITTLE THING (5) raced below her best last time when sixth over 2042m at Ballarat, beaten 8 lengths, but hasn't been in 56 grade since the win here, over this trip, four runs back. That made it two from two at the track, so she obviously loves the place. MORISU OJO (1) hasn't started since the G1 VRC Oaks and while she failed to beat a runner home there, earlier in spring she was beaten just 1-3/4 lengths in an 1800m Listed event the start after breaking her maiden over 1600m. This looks a suitable first-up option. ONE MORE STAR (4) is back from BM70 grade and while beaten 9 lengths that day, she was not far off the runner-up and looks much better placed here. LUCKY COMPASS (8) held on well to finish second last time out over 1512m at Geelong after leading for much of the way. Well-placed and worth including. PARVATI PARTY (3) is yet to place in 7 first-up runs but is in new hands and did win a recent trial, so might be an improver this time.",
